---
description: Enforces Next.js 15 app router structure, server components, and project organization
globs: app/**/*.tsx, app/**/*.ts
---
This rule helps with:
@app/components - Ensures proper component organization and structure
@app/routes - Guides route file placement and naming
@app/api - Enforces API route conventions
@app/layout - Maintains consistent layout structure
@app/page - Follows page component patterns
@lib - Organizes utility functions and shared code
@hooks - Structures custom React hooks properly
@types - Maintains TypeScript type definitions
middleware.ts - project middleware

Key tasks:
- Creating new pages and routes
- Implementing server components
- Managing API endpoints
- Organizing shared components
- Handling data fetching
- Implementing layouts
- Setting up middleware
- Managing app-wide state